summary: A customer calls the I T C with a complaint and is transferred to a Tamil-speaking agent. The customer explains that they bought a Sita Interest box and wants to know if they can use a different model for cutting a leopard print. The agent explains that it is not necessary for the competition and that they can use the provided stick and bag. The customer also mentions that they saw an animal prevention lawyer and wonders if they can sue the company. The agent offers to connect them with the feedback team, and the customer provides their valuable suggestion. The feedback team thanks the customer for their suggestion and assures them that it will be passed on to the concerned team. The customer and agent conclude the call with pleasantries.
speaker_a_summary: The caller wants to know about an image of a movie poster for the film 'Sita' starring a leopard and wants to confirm that the film's name is indeed 'Sita'. The ITC employee will forward this feedback to the relevant team and informs the caller that they will receive a reply from the Feedback Team regarding their suggestion. The caller thanks the employee for their valuable suggestion and the conversation ends with good wishes and pleasantries.
speaker_b_summary: The conversation is between a person who seems to be in a shop, and another person, who is probably their supervisor or manager and is called Lawrence. The person in the shop is calling to Lawrence about returning two items: a Sita interest box and a sweet potato, probably because they are not needed, and to ask for advice in regards to returning those items and getting a refund. The person in the shop also mentions a third item, a cheesecake, which they bought yesterday, and which has a Tamil name which is spelled out as "Cheetha".
